cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual recognition tasks. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new framework for learning from noisy labels. Additionally, it may belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it mentions using label relations in knowledge graphs. Finally, it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it proposes new benchmark datasets in different domains.
